    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nBlockwise forced motion doesn't work consistently for single character during delete/change.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Add line `ab`\r\n3. Put cursor on `a`.\r\n4. Create a mark on it with `mx`.\r\n5. Type ``d<C-v>`x``.\r\n\r\nNote: the issue is also reproducible with change operator `c`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCharacter `a` is deleted. Same as after `<C-v>`xd` (delete visual selection).\r\n\r\nThis is not entirely predictable for these reasons:\r\n- Yanking in this situation (``y<C-v>`x``) does work.\r\n- Charwise forced mode (``dv`x``) does work.\r\n- If mark is over `b`, then typing ``d<C-v>`x`` will delete both characters leaving no way to actually delete single character in blockwise forced mode.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-772+g0211f889b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes (9.1.1676)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.4.8-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
